# Clean Architecture Enforcement

Apply this quality gate to every non-trivial change set.

- Prevent architectural drift (duplicated logic, oversized routers, parallel implementations).
- Prefer shared abstractions over one-off implementations.
- Keep transport concerns in routers and business logic in feature services.
- Propose explicit refactor stories if decomposition opportunities are identified.
